No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFAF6A10FA549E72143AB340" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFAF6A10FA549E72143AB340" blockId="84.[1447,2656,1227,2281]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFAF6A10FA549E721906B37E" bold="true" box="[1448,1798,2091,2124]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. Thomas's Big-eared Brown Bat is not abundant locally, and its habitatis in significant decline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
